content.body:
### Shop 205/65R16 Tire Size 205/65R16 is a tire size that’s often used on medium and large sedans such as the Chevrolet Malibu, Hyundai Sonata, Toyota Camry, Kia Optima, and Honda Accord. Commonly used as daily drivers, these vehicles are often at their best when paired with all-season tires, and might roll out of the factory with a brand new set of Firestone FT140, Goodyear Assurance Fuel Max, Hankook Kinergy GT (H436), [Kumho Solus TA31](https://simpletire.com/brands/kumho-tires/solus-ta31), or Continental ContiProContact tires attached. Popular vehicles: 2016-2022 Chevrolet Malibu
2011-2021 Hyundai Sonata
2012-2021 Toyota Camry
2011-2020 Kia Optima
2013-2017 Honda Accord Most drivers use all-season tires thanks to their ability to perform well in dry, wet, and light winter weather conditions. Check out the [Continental TrueContact Tour](https://simpletire.com/brands/continental-tires/truecontact-tour), Pirelli P4 Four Seasons Plus, Yokohama Avid Ascend LX, or Nexen Aria AH7 if you’re looking for a new set of 205/65R16 all-season tires. A newer tire type, all-weather tires are slightly better than all-season tires in winter weather conditions thanks to their more flexible rubber compound. If you live in an area that receives moderate to heavy snow and ice and want a tire that’s better built to handle these elements than an all-season, take a look at the Michelin Cross Climate2 A/W, General Altimax 365AW, Nokian WR G4, or [Toyo Celsisus](https://simpletire.com/brands/toyo-tires/celsius). The winter months often bring ice, slush, snow, and lower temperatures with it, and all of these elements can make driving more difficult than it needs to be as your tires struggle to grip the road. Winter tires are built with a flexible rubber compound that allows for consistent grip in lower temperatures and plenty of other technology such as sipes that increase traction on ice and snow. Consider winter tires such as the [Bridgestone Blizzak WS90](https://simpletire.com/brands/bridgestone-tires/blizzak-ws90), Falken Winterpeak F-Ice , Kumho WinterCraft Ice WI31, or Nitto NT-SN2 for extra traction in ice and heavy snow. Whether you drive a Chevrolet Malibu, Toyota Camry, Honda Accord or something else, SimpleTire has a set of 205/65R16 tires that meets your needs at a great price!
